  "texts": [
    "Listing 1: Example of Using LangChain to Invoke an LLM 1 from langchain.",
    "llms import OpenAI 2 llm = OpenAI (model = ' ' gpt -4 ' ', temperature =0.9) 3 text = '' Tell me a short joke about cakes. '",
    "' 4 print (llm (text))",
    "While the example provided is rudimentary, in real-world applications, interactions with the LLM are not isolated but rather constitute a series of steps where intermediate results necessitate logical processing for initiating the subsequent step.",
    "This sequence of combined interactions is termed as Chains, which typically involves integrations with one or more model providers, data storage systems, and APIs, among others."
  ]
}